In this video, I unbox and compare every budget iPhone ever released—starting with the iPhone 5C, Apple’s first attempt at a budget smartphone back in 2013. From there, I dive into the iPhone SE lineup, including knock-off versions from shady eBay sellers. And of course, I put them all up against the latest so-called budget model, the iPhone 16e, which has been heavily criticized for being a terrible value. Is the iPhone 16e really Apple’s worst budget phone ever, or have past models been just as bad? Watch to find out!

0:00 Unboxing ever
title: Apple’s "Budget" iPhones Keep Getting Worse...
